title: For Sale:  9MM Walther PPS M2 w/ 3 mags - only 500 rounds fired w/ original case/packaging/lock/sticky holster/other extras
postcontent: I am selling my Walther PPS M2 pistol. This gun was purchased late December 2017, so it's only a few months old. This pistol is great and would be perfect for CCW use like I had been using it for, but I'm looking to help finance an AR9 build and I also plan on jumping up to the larger Walther PPQ as my carry gun and also so I add a suppressor to the threaded PPQ for home defense use. Nothing wrong with the pistol, in fact I love it. If I had more money I'd be keeping it. It's a great shooter, awesome ergonomics - which is the reason I bought it, feels perfect in the hand. The Glock 43 felt like crap to me and the Shield 2.09 felt just slightly less good in my hands, so I went with the PPS. I've put approximately 500 rounds through it, all brass case ammo. 3 total range trips, 30 minute sessions each time. Thankfully it never had to be fired when carrying concealed. Pistol was cleaned well after each range trip. The PPS M2 will come with:-Pistol-3 total magazines: 6/7/8 rounders. That's 2 extra mags that normally run $40ish a piece. *The 8 round mag was given to me by another, it's in perfect condition but it may or may not have had more rounds through it, a stranger on the internet gave me it for shipping costs and a small AR part in exchange. Looked new enough when I got it, just adding this in the interest of full disclosure-I've installed rubberized talon grips onto the pistol, and I'll install them onto any future gun I own. My groupings improved just from installing them. They make it so you have a lockjaw grip on the gun while firing. The PPS ergonomics plus talon grips leads to a great shooting gun. Love this thing-Sticky Brand Holster. Uses friction to keep it in place, and I used this for my concealed carry. I never had any issues with it sliding, won't budge in jeans and stays still even with athletic shorts. Plus side is it's also comfortable enough so that holster contact w/ skin is nothing to worry about-Original Walther storage case-Cable Lock-Red Chamber Flag - might need this at some shooting ranges*I'll toss in any 9mm-specific cleaning supplies I have on hand if you ask, some people already have cleaning kits and some don't.
